t also for non-scholars, Jewish women, and even non-Jews. Philosophical and kabbalistic thought joined together to form a model of religious experience attractive to a broad audience, laying an ideological foundation for the missionary messianism that was to become a hallmark of Habad in the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHabad. 0aHasidism. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Religious Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Kabbalah. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Mysticism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2019z978311149143140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438475561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438475561/original  a978-3-11-149143-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles